nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|And finally let's talk about the heart lead. It was correct if you play standard leads. You lead 10 from K109. But some people play coded tens and nines. If you play that the lead of the 9 shows either the 10 and a higher honor (not the J) or nothing higher than the 9.|
PG| ***** 14 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|On this hand playing coded 9s doesn't really matter as it turns out since, once the @HQ wins, it is pretty clear that East holds the K109. But on other hands, coded tens and nines give partner more information about opening leader's holding.|
